ents embody our desire to keep passengers and cargo safe while providing you a silent ride the parts must be strong and stiff enough to withstand high loads but designed to achieve weight reduction through design optimization we are able to engineer and manufacture durable and lightweight multimaterial solutions using our proprietary nvh laminates we can reduce noise and eliminate the need for additional sounddamping materials further reducing the weight of the vehicle shiloh’s solutions include dash and floor panels plenum trunk floors spare wheel and folding seat tubs door systems wheelhouse roof panels instrument panel beams seat supports seat back frames seat risers and center console frames chassis systems shiloh’s chassis systems provide a strong foundation for the vehicle’s driveline and body these systems require high strength to support and transfer loads through the body of the vehicle our aluminum squeeze casting process produces high integrity thickwalled components that can replace cast iron offering an efficient durable and lightweight solution laser welded blanks can offer weight reduction in frames without compromising strength shiloh’s solutions include cross members frame rails axle carriers tubes covers housings bearing caps clutch housings brake components steering column housings knuckles links master cylinders powertrain systems shiloh’s powertrain systems offers oems and suppliers sustainable multimaterial solutions to reduce weight noise and vibration using our advanced engineering design and simulation capabilities we can provide the optimum solution for every product whether it is cast stamped or a complex assembly incorporating both with the added benefit of noise and vibration reduction using our proprietary nvh laminates shiloh’s solutions include planetary carriers clutch housings transmission gear housings engine valve covers valve bodies rocker arm spacers heat shields exhaust manifolds cones baffles mufflers shields engine oil pans transmission fluid pans front covers transmissions covers latest newsshiloh industries develops lightweight aluminum cast rear solid beam axle housingshiloh industries inc announces pricing of common stock offeringshiloh industries inc announces common stock offeringshiloh industries awarded with gm supplier quality excellence awardshiloh industries added to russell ® index read more interested in learning more about our technology and innovations be the first to know share your email address with us and we’ll keep you updated full contact form send about us  shiloh industries about us about safe silent strong sustainable shiloh industries inc nasdaq shlo is a global innovative solutions provider focusing on lightweighting technologies that provide environmental and safety benefits to the mobility market  the company designs and manufactures products within body structure chassis and powertrain systems leveraging one of the broadest portfolios in the industry shiloh’s multicomponent multimaterial solutions are comprised of a variety of alloys in aluminum magnesium and steel grades along with its proprietary line of noise and vibration reducing shilohcore acoustic laminate products  the strategic blanklight® castlight® and stamplight® brands combine to maximize lightweighting solutions without compromising safety or performance the company has over  dedicated employees with operations sales and technical centers throughout asia europe and north america lightweighting without compromise® safety is something we take seriously at shiloh in fact it is one of our hallmarks our products are designed and manufactured with the highest precision to meet or exceed the strictest quality standards in the industry our crossfunctional teams and dedicated safety managers ensure all projects meet ts and apqp standards ensuring only the highest quality design development and production to ensure our products are of the highest quality our engineers use our proprietary technologies to test and validate parts in accordance with our quality control standards we test thermal and fatigue requirements fea and fluid dynamics cfd along with metallurgical spectrological and tensilecompression to offer the highest quality lightweight products without compromising strength and safety our products are highly engineered to add the required strength where necessary while reducing material weight where it is only required we also offer dynamic testing of materials through our industry partners for added validation for specific customer needs we use only highpurity highductility alloys which includes alloy modification to attain the best mix of castability die life strength and stiffness reducing vehicle weight is one of the automotive industry’s greatest opportunities to improve fuel efficiency and economy and lightweighting can help ensure automakers met those increasingly tougher standards however reducing vehicle mass can magnify noise and vibration being transmitted into the vehicle’s interior to alleviate this obstacle our patented shilohcore acoustic laminate solutions can reduce interior noise by up to db in many applications developed from our proprietary chemistry and manufacturing processes our patented shilohcore acoustic laminate is a viscoelastic constrained layer application that dampens noise and vibration and minimizes costs without adding unnecessary mass sustainability is at the core of our business model automakers are under increased pressure and various government demands to meet and exceed the everincreasing global emission standards in an effort to decrease greenhouse gases to aid in this initiative our innovative lightweighting technologies improve material consumption and co emissions through the reduction of part weight and overall vehicle weight resulting in an increase in vehicle fuel efficiency adding to our sustainability efforts we go to great lengths to ensure our manufacturing processes and products are designed to reduce landfill waste as a result over half of our facilities are landfillfree with the goal that all our capable facilities will be landfillfree by  lightweighting with benefits® latest newsshiloh industries develops lightweight aluminum cast rear solid beam axle housingshiloh industries inc announces pricing of common stock offeringshiloh industries inc announces common stock offeringshiloh industries awarded with gm supplier quality excellence awardshiloh industries added to russell ® index read more interested in learning more about our technology and innovations be the first to know share your email address with us and we’ll keep you updated full contact form send microsoft personalized ad preferences to opt out of personalized ads in this browser your browser history must allow firstparty and thirdparty cookies and you must have your browsing experience set to not delete browsing history on exit instructions for enabling cookies and configuring your browsing history may be available in your browsers settings privacy or help documentation sign in hold on… we’re sorry but this didn’t work you can’t turn off personalized ads right now because your browser is currently blocking thirdparty cookies we can help you fix this issue let’s get started depending on what browser you use open options or settings make sure that thirdparty cookies are not blocked anymore to find out how search your browser’s help revisit httpchoicemicrosoftcomoptout and then on the “personalized ads in this browser” tile click off ext about our ads to create a more customized online experience some of the ads you may receive on microsoft websites and apps are tailored to your previous activities searches and site visits youre in control and heres where you can make the advertising choice thats right for you ext where can i learn more about advertising on microsoft websites and apps microsoft partners with oath appnexus and other third party service providers to help present customized content and display