roduction die cast parts have highly repeatable properties and tolerances typical lead time tooling   weeks samples   weeks production qty k   weeks tooling life expectancy k shots prototype tooling the term “soft tool” is used to describe a die cast tool made out of p steel the p steel is softer than h steel and thus yields parts in less time with a decrease in tooling cost attributed to the ability to run faster feed rates when cnc machining the tool typically a p tool can yield  parts before showing any significant wear typical lead time tooling   weeks samples   weeks production qty    days tooling life expectancy k shots materials we routinely pour a broad range nonferrous materials the following are some of the most common alloys being used aluminum die casting alloys a a a and kalloy magnesium die casting alloys include azd and amb zinc die casting alloys include za za and za copper alloy die castings design criteria as cast tolerance as tight as  ” post machining available for tighter tolerance applications standard tolerance of  ” for the first inch and ” each additional inch typical surface finish of ra  microinch as cast post machining available for higher quality finishes minimum draft   degrees minimum wall thickness  ” thinner wall thickness possible with alternative processes what our customers say “without spectron our project would not have been as successful as it was they demonstrated the teamwork knowledge and ‘cando’ attitude needed to pull off a difficult order” preferred vendor for shiloh industries inc  valley city  medina county  steel dr company directory and business data solutions about kompass register login login × please fill in your login and password register login forgot your password  english contact kompass north america please contact one of our team of experts from monday to friday between am and pm or by email     contact us search across  million selected companies in more than  countries or all suppliers one company recherche